      <strong>General Guidance for Repair vs Replace:</strong><br>
      If the cost of repairing an existing electrical motor is more than <strong>65%</strong> the cost of replacing it, replacement is usually more cost-effective-especially if the new component is more efficient. But, other factors like design, age, size, lead times, and application requirements must be considered.
    </div>
